// Correctness arc 5 (h), compound arm: the decl gate FOLDS the RHS
// (goo_fold_const_int_ctx) and judges the folded value, so constant
// arithmetic that lands out of range rejects even though each literal
// individually fits. NOTE the deliberate asymmetry with var decls:
// `var v int8 = 200 + 100` is still accepted by the per-literal adapter
// design (a documented deviation — see adapt_untyped_int_operand); const
// decls had no gate at all, so they get the fold-based Go-correct rule
// with no accepted-program to preserve.
package main

func main() {
	const k int8 = 200 + 100
	println(k)
}
